<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-27T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-27T07:00:00-05:00" n="69" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 793.94/214.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-27T20:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1915—8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Further Japanese demands reported today include administrative powers in
                            South Manchuria and special rights respecting the nationalized iron
                            deposits throughout China.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
